VTools also have consequences.
p21
aVAt least since the Industrial Revolution, the world of design has been dominated
p22
aVby the rigors of manufacturing and mass production.
p23
aVAssembly lines have dictated a world made of parts,
p24
aVframing the imagination of designers and architects
p25
aVwho have been trained to think about their objects as assemblies
p26
aVof discrete parts with distinct functions.
