aa(lp28
VBut you don't find homogenous material assemblies in nature.
p29
aVTake human skin, for example.
p30
aVOur facial skins are thin with large pores.
p31
aVOur back skins are thicker, with small pores.
p32
aVOne acts mainly as filter,
p33
aVthe other mainly as barrier,
p34
aVand yet it's the same skin: no parts, no assemblies.
p35
aVIt's a system that gradually varies its functionality
p36
aVby varying elasticity.
